	volume = {43},
	abstract = {Popular reactions toward government efforts to control the recent cholera epidemic in
Northeast Brazil are evaluated. Intensive ethnographic interviews and participant-observation in two
urban slums OCavelas), reveal a high level of resistance on the part of impoverished residents towards olficial
cholera control interventions and mass media campaigns. "Non-compliance" with recommended regimens
